Move four species of Mirafra larks (Fawn-colored, Foxy, Pink-breasted, Sabota) and four species of Certhilauda larks (Karoo, Dune, Barlow's, Red) to the (new) genus Calendulauda (de Juana et al 2004, Hockey, Dean & Ryan 2005, Alstr÷m et al 2013)

Position of Scissor-tailed Kite provisional in absence of molecular data

Separate Coccopygia waxbills from Estrilda (Payne 2010)

Restore Cochabamba Mountain Finch and Tucuman Mountain Finch to Compsospiza from Poospiza (Klicka et al 2007; SACC 366 reversed previous decision to lump)

Move Straight-billed Woodcreeper and Zimmer's Woodcreeper from Xiphorhynchus to Dendroplex (Aleixo 2002, Aleixo et al 2007, SACC 316)

The traditional genus Pipra is polyphyletic (Tello et al 2009); Dixiphia is tentatively used for the second clade.
Molecular data place Crab-plover as relative of coursers and pratincoles (Glareolidae) (Pereira and Baker 2010)

Move Eremomela to the Cisticolidae (Johansson et al 2008)
Move Erpornis from babblers (Timaliidae) to vireos (Vireonidae) (Reddy and Cracraft 2007, Reddy 2008); Change English name (tentatively) to White-bellied Erpornis; it is not a Yuhina
Move from Incertae sedis to new family Erythrocercidae, after Scotocercidae (Fregin et al 2012)
Adoption of Erythropitta follows Irestedt et al (2006)
Relationships of Erythrotriorchis goshawks uncertain
Eupodotis is biphyletic, with rueppellii, humilis and vigorsii forming a deep branch and the three other species grouped with Afrotis (Pitra et al. 2002,Fjeldss comm, REF).
Separation of Eupsittula spp from Aratinga follows Remsen et al (2013)
Eurillas bulbuls separated from Andropadus following Johansson et al (2007)
The eared nightjars Eurostopodus are the basal to rest of the Caprimulgidae, and thus placed first in the sequence of the genera (Barrowclough et al 2006, Larsen et al. 2007).
King Quail and Blue Quail are moved from Coturnix to Excalfactoria (Crowe et al 2006, Christidis &á Boles 2008)

Gampsonyx is sister to Elanus. Both genera are basal to all other Accipitridae (Griffiths et al 2004, Wink & Sauer-Gnrth 2004)
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae

Former Geotrygon is paraphyletic. Classification below including Leptotrygon and Zentrygon follows Johnson & Weckstein (2011), Banks et al (2013), NACC 2014-C-3, SACC 640
Expand Geranoaetus to include Buteo polyosoma and B. albicaudatus (SACC 460)
Sister to Trichoglossus assemblage (Joseph et al 2012)
Move Green-backed Honeyeater from Timeliopsis to Glycichaera (Driskell & Christidis 2004, Higgins et al 2008, Christidis &á Boles 2008)

Separate Madagascar Starling from Saroglossa to Hartlaubius; resequence to precede Violet-backed Starling (Lovette & Rubenstein 2007)
Genus Heinrichia transferred from Turdidae to Muscicapidae/Saxicolinae  (Sangster et al 2010, Zuccon & Ericson 2010; full revision of Muscicapidae to come)

Move Hemipus from the Campephagidae to the Tephrodornithidae (Moyle et al 2006)

Separate Purple-headed Starling and Copper-tailed Starling from Lamprotornis to Hylopsar; resequence to precede Lampropsar (Lovette & Rubenstein 2007)
Relationships of Icteria to Parulidae uncertain (Lovette et al 2010)

The whistling species of Tockus are separated to Lophoceros (Gonzalez et al. 2013ab)

Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae

Neosenas must be treated as masculine. David & Gregory, 2008
Separation of Nesoptilotis honeyeaters follows Nyßri and Joseph (2011)

Separate Old World species of Spizaetus into Nisaetus (Helbig et al. 2005, Haring et al. 2007)
Separate Black-bellied Starling from Lamprotornis to Notopholia; resequence to precede Lampropsar (Lovette & Rubenstein 2007)

Separate Black-collared Apalis and Ruwenzori Apalis from Apalis to Oreolais; related to Urolais, Schistolais and Artisornis (Nguembock et al 2008). Change English name?

Move Paradoxornis species to end of sequence of parrotbills

MOVE Parkerthraustes to Thraupidae from Cardinalidae (Klicka et al. 2007; AOU 2009)

Separate Rosy Starling from Sturnus to Pastor (Lovette et al 2008, Zuccon et al 2008)
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae
Peltops species are basal members of the Cracticinae,  now a subfamily of the Artamidae (Kearns et al 2013, cf Norman et al 2009)
Separate the following seven species of Aimophila sparrows to Peucaea (DaCosta et al 2009, NACC 2009-A-12a)
See Pulgßrin-R et al 2013 for species phylogeny. Change English name to Yellow Grosbeak.
Phibalura Is a cotinga, sister to Ampelion and Doliornis (Berv & Prum 2014)

The asities and sunbird-asities, formerly placed in the family Philepittidae are broadbills and now included in that family to avoid rendering the Eurylaimidae paraphyletic (Prum 1993; Irestedt et al. 2006)
Retained in Philohydor following Lanyon 1986 and Fitzpatrick 2004, contra placement in Pitangus by SACC and AOU (1998)
Pholidornis is a sylvioid tentatively allied to Hylia and the Cettiidae (Sefc et al. 2003, Fuchs et al. 2006, Johannson et al 2008); Fregin et al 2012 suggest assignment to Hyliidae.

Mountain Tailorbird and Rufous-headed Tailorbird are not related to Orthotomus (Cisticolidae); assigned instead to Phyllergates [Cettiidae] (Alstr÷m et al 2006, Ryan et al 2006, Nguembock et al 2007)

Phyllomyias is polyphyletic with at least two clades of species; nomenclature revisions will include return to use of Tyranniscus for one set of species (Fitzpatrick 2004, Tello et al 2009; SACC; Harshman 2009)
Zoonomen, IBC. Original spelling. Piezorhina is an unjustified emendation.
Separate Moorland Chat from other species of  Cercomela/Oenanthe to Pinarochroa (Outlaw et al 2010, Aliabadian et al 2012)
Piprites is traditionally grouped with the manakins (Pipridae), but both Tello et al. (2009) and Ohlson et al. (2008) place it within Tyrannidae, possibly in a basal position (Harshman 2009)
MOVE Piranga spp from Thraupidae to Cardinalidae (Burns et al. 2003, Klicka et al. 2007,NACC 2008-B-1, SACC 318)
Pitohui sensu stricto is sister to Oriolus (J°nsson et al 2008, Dumbacher 2013)
The two species of Pittasoma are sister to gnateaters Conopophaga and resequenced to be in this family (Rice 2005, SACC)
Camarhynchus crassirostris is now assigned to Platyspiza (Burns et al. 2002, SACC)
Platysteira species sequence follows Njabo et al 2008
The Pluvialis plovers are members of the traditional plover family Charadriidae (Baker et al 2012,  cf Baker et al. 2007)
STET: SACC keeps bristle tyrants in Phylloscartes but needs proposal to update to Pogonotriccus (Fitzpatrick 2004).
Polyboroides is a basal taxon within Accipitridae, sister to Gypohierax, Pernix and related taxa (Wink & Sauer-Gnrth 2004, Lerner & Mindell 2005).
Previously Carpodacus, Dark-breasted Rosefinch is assigned to Procarduelis (Zuccon et al 2012)
Aechmorhynchusáis synonymized witháProsobonia (Cibois et al 2012)
Conserve Prosopeia Bonaparte, 1854 for the Fijian shining parrots which at times is replaced by Pyrrhulopsis Reichenbach 1850 (Schodde et al, ICZN case 3640, 2013.)
Separate Mulga Parrot and allies from Psephotus to Psephotellus (Joseph et a 2012)
Transfer 4 species of Alethe to Pseudalethe (Sangster et al 2010)
Four related species of Asthenes separated to Pseudasthenes (Derryberry et al. 2010, SACC 432)
Pseudoalcippe Hill Babblers belong in the Sylviidae (Cibois 2003)
Genus Psilopogon takes precedence over Megalaima and must used given that Fire-tufted Barbet is imbedded in the latter as sister to Great Barbet (Moyle et al 2004, H&M4)
Separation of Psittacara spp from Aratinga follows Remsen et al (2013)
Shrike-babblers are Old World vireos (Reddy 2008); resequence
Revert spelling of Ptilogonys to the original spelling Ptiliogonys. Auk 130:566. AOU 54th supplement. 2013.
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae

Ptilopachus partridges of Africa are related to New World quails (Odontophoridae) and in turn to the guineafowl (Numididae), not to members of Phasianidae (Crowe et al. 2006, Crowe 2010, Cohen et al 2012). See also Bowie et al 2013 recommendation to treat as a subfamily Ptilopachinae.
Jewel-babblers and quail-thrushes are sister taxa, not related to whipbirds (Norman et al 2009); revised family taxonomy to come
Separation of Ptilotula honeyeaters follows Nyßri and Joseph (2011)
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae
The genus Puffinus is polyphyletic; some lists separate pacificus, bulleri, griseus, tenuirostris, creatopus, carneipes and gravis to Ardenna (Penhallurick & Wink 2004, H&M4, HBW/BirdLife)
Move  White-fronted Honeyeater from Phylidonyris to Purnella following White-plumed Honeyeater (Driskell & Christidis 2004, Higgins et al 2008, Christidis &  Boles 2008)

MOVE the following 4 rail species from Rallina to Rallicula (Christidis & Boles 2008); Rallicula rails may be related to flufftails and Canirallus rails in the Sarothruridae (Livezey 1998, but see Garcia et al 2014)
Phlogothraupis is merged with Ramphocelus (NACC, Dickinson 2003); note gender agreement
Rhabdornis "Creepers" of the Philippines are related to Aplonis starlings and not separable into their own family (Lovette et al 2008; Zucco et al 2008)
The "wrinkled" species of Aceros are separated to the genus Rhabdotorrhinus (Gonzalez et al. 2013ab)
MOVE Rhopophilus to Sylviidae positioned near Paradoxornis (Gelang et al 2009, Olsson et al 2013b)
Separate Tumbes Sparrow and Stripe-capped Sparrow from Aimophila to Rhynchospiza (DaCosta et al 2009, SACC 456)
DNA analyses support separation of Podargus inexpectatus to a monotypic genus Rigidipenna (Cleere, Kratter, Steadman, Braun, Huddleston, Filardi, & Dutson, 2007, BLI, TOL)
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae
Robsonius is sister to Locustellidae, not a babbler (Oliveros et al 2012). Change group name to Ground Warbler (Hosner et al 2013).
Saltators may be related to tanagers not grosbeaks, but nodes need better resolution (see Klicka et al. 2007; AOU 2009)
Sapheopipo groups with Dendrocopos (Fuchs et al 2007)
MOVE Eurylaimus steerii and E. samarensis to Sarcophanops (Dekker & Dickinson 2000, Irestedt et al 2006)
Separate Winifred's Warbler from Bathmocercus to Scepomycter; move both genera to Cisticolidae (Ryan et al 2006)
Scotocerca is sister to Cettiidae. Move from Incertae sedis to family Scotocercidae) (Alstr÷m et al 2011c, Fregin et al 2012, Olsson et al 2013b) cf Barhoum and Burns 2002)
Semnornis barbets are treated as separate family Semnornithidae to reflect phylogeny (SACC 7, NACC 2010).
Generic assignments of New World taxa, formerly placed in Caprimulgus, are revised following SACC 522 based on Han et al 2010.
Replace Dendroica with Setophaga (36 species + 2 Parula sp) (AOU 2011)
Silvicultrix has often been submerged within Ochthoeca (in Fluvicolini), but the two are not closest relatives (Tello et al. 2009; Harshman 2009).
Separation of Sittiparus spp from Poecile follows Johansson et al 2013
Spotted Wren-Babbler moved to monotypic Elachuridae, Elachura.
Separate Spotted Dove and Laughing Dove from Streptopelia to Spilopelia, not Stigmatopelia (Schodde 1997; Penhallurick correspondence, cf Cheke 2005, BLI)
Previously in Carduelis,  New World goldfinches and siskins are restored to Spinus (NACC 2008-A-9B) or Sporagra (SACC 488);  sequence of Spinus based on Arnaiz-Villena et al (2012)
Separate Red-billed Starling and White-cheeked Starling from Sturnus to Spodiopsar (Lovette et al 2008, Zuccon et al 2008)
Stachyridopsis species are removed from Stachyris (Collar & Robson 2007).
Stelgidillas bulbuls separated from Andropadus following Johansson et al (2007)
See Bridge et al 2005 for revision of tern genera
Additional species of Stigmatura complex await resolution and formal description (fide B. Whitney)
Separation of Stomiopera honeyeaters follows Nyßri and Joseph (2011)
Separate five starling species ( White-shouldered, Chestnut-tailed, White-headed, Malabar, and Brahminy) from Sturnus to Sturnia (Lovette et al 2008, Zuccon et al 2008)
Separate White-faced Starling from Sturnus to Sturnornis (Lovette et al 2008, Zuccon et al 2008)
Move Black Honeyeater from Certhionyx to Sugomel (Driskell & Christidis 2004, Higgins et al 2008, Christidis &á Boles 2008)
Separate 19 species of Monarcha to Symposiachrus (Filardi & Smith 2005, Christidis &á Boles 2008)
Generic assignments of New World taxa, formerly placed in Caprimulgus, are revised following SACC #522 based on Han et al 2010.
Move Bolivia Earthcreeper and Chaco Earthcreeper from Upucerthia to Tarphonomus (Chesser & Brumfield, 2007, SACC 323)
Genetic data place Terenotriccus in the Tityridae (Ohlson et al. 2008, Tello et al 2009)
Separation of Blue-crowned Parakeet from Aratinga to Thectocercus follows Remsen et al (2013, SACC 578); see also Urantowka et al (2012). H&M4 include in Psittacara
Move Tickellia from Sylviidae to Cettiidae (Alstr÷m et al 2006, Johansson et al 2008)
Moveá Lappet-faced Vulture from Aegypius to Torgos (Dickinson 2003, BLI)
Two species of nativehen are moved from Gallinula to Tribonyx (Livezey 1998, Christidis &  Boles 2008)
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Pellorneidae
Moveá White-headed Vulture from Aegypius to Trigonoceps (Dickinson 2003, BLI)
Trochalopteron laughingthrushes are clade of babblers that are phylogenetically separate from Garrulax (Gelang et al 2009)
Dusky Crested Flycatcher, White-bellied Crested Flycatcher, & White-tailed Crested Flycatcher transferred from Trochocercus to Elminia (Dickinson 2003, Sinclair & Ryan 2003, Coates et al 2006 )
Genus transferred from Timaliidae to new babbler family Leiothrichidae
Piopio Turnagra belongs with Old World orioles (Oriolidae), not with bowerbirds (Ptilonorhynchidae) (Johansson et al 2011, cf Christidis et al 1996)
Uromyias resurrected based on recent molecular studies. DuBay & Witt, 2012, SACC 525
Separate four species of Jungle Flycatchers from Rhinomyias to Vauriella (Sangster et al 2010)
Separate Scale-backed Antbird from Hylophylax to new genus Willisornis (Brumfield et al 2007, Agne &á Pacheco 2007, SACC 495)
Relationships of Xenoligea to Parulidae uncertain (Lovette et al 2010)
Chloropipo is now assigned to Xenopipo (Prum 1992, SACC)
Move Yuhina species to Zosteropidae from Timaliidae (Cibois et al 2003, Moyle et al 2009); recognition of separate clades under review.
Relationships of Zeledonia to Parulidae uncertain (Lovette et al 2010)
Resequence Zenaida to follow Zentrygon/Ectopistes (Johnson & Weckstein 2011, Banks et al 2013)
Zentrygon is a new genus for the clade of quail-dove species that are related to Zenaida doves (Banks et al, 2013).
Resequence species of Zosterops to align with phylogenetic structure (Moyle et al 2009 )
